headline: MET Q2 Deep Dive: Variable Investment Income and Underwriting Pressure Shape Results
summary: Global insurance giant MetLife (NYSE:MET) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales falling 4.1% year on year to $17.92 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.02 per share was 6.3% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
